    "### Step 3. Pre-process and extract the features"

   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def disp_data(feature1,feature2):\n",

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Different Error calculations to asses the model for training set"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "##### 1. Sum of Squared Error (SSE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Sum of Squared Error (SSE) : 665.99\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sum = 0   \n",
    "n = len(x_train)  \n",
    "for i in range (0,n):   \n",
    "  diff = y_train[i] - y_train_pred[i]   \n",
    "  squ_diff = diff**2   \n",
    "  sum = sum + squ_diff   \n",
    "Train_SSE = round(sum,2)\n",
    "print(\"Sum of Squared Error (SSE) :\",Train_SSE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "##### 2. Mean Squared Error (MSE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Mean Squared Error (MSE) : 0.31\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "Train_MSE = round(sum/n,2)\n",
    "print(\"Mean Squared Error (MSE) :\",Train_MSE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "##### 3. Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE) : 0.56\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "Train_RMSE = round(np.sqrt(Train_MSE),2)\n",
    "print(\"Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE) :\",Train_RMSE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "##### 4. Mean Absolute Error (MAE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Mean Absolute Error (MAE) : 0.45\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sum = 0   \n",
    "n = len(x_train)  \n",
    "for i in range (0,n):   \n",
    "  diff = y_train[i] - y_train_pred[i]   \n",
    "  sum = sum + np.abs(diff)   \n",
    "Train_MAE = round(sum/n,2)\n",
    "print(\"Mean Absolute Error (MAE) :\",Train_MAE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "##### 5. Mean Absolute Percentage Error (MAPE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 28,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Mean Absolute Percentage Error (MAPE) : 0.02\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sum = 0   \n",
    "n = len(x_train)  \n",
    "for i in range (0,n):   \n",
    "  diff = (y_train[i] - y_train_pred[i])/y_train[i]\n",
    "  sum = sum + np.abs(diff)  \n",
    "Train_MAPE = round(sum/n*100,2)\n",
    "print(\"Mean Absolute Percentage Error (MAPE) :\",Train_MAPE) "
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "### Different Error calculations to asses the model for the test set"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "##### 1. Sum of Squared Error (SSE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 36,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Sum of Squared Error (SSE) : 171.63\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sum = 0   \n",
    "n = len(x_test)  \n",
    "for i in range (0,n):   \n",
    "  diff = y_test[i] - y_test_pred[i]   \n",
    "  squ_diff = diff**2   \n",
    "  sum = sum + squ_diff   \n",
    "Test_SSE = round(sum,2)\n",
    "print(\"Sum of Squared Error (SSE) :\",Test_SSE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "##### 2. Mean Squared Error (MSE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Mean Squared Error (MSE) : 0.32\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "Test_MSE = round(sum/n,2)\n",
    "print(\"Mean Squared Error (MSE) :\",Test_MSE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "##### 3. Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 38,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE) : 0.57\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "Test_RMSE = round(np.sqrt(Test_MSE),2)\n",
    "print(\"Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE) :\",Test_RMSE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "##### 4. Mean Absolute Error (MAE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 39,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Mean Absolute Error (MAE) : 0.46\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sum = 0   \n",
    "n = len(x_test)  \n",
    "for i in range (0,n):   \n",
    "  diff = y_test[i] - y_test_pred[i]   \n",
    "  sum = sum + np.abs(diff)   \n",
    "Test_MAE = round(sum/n,2)\n",
    "print(\"Mean Absolute Error (MAE) :\",Test_MAE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "##### 5. Mean Absolute Percentage Error (MAPE)"

  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 40,

   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Mean Absolute Percentage Error (MAPE) : 0.02\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sum = 0   \n",
    "n = len(x_test)  \n",
    "for i in range (0,n):   \n",
    "  diff = (y_test[i] - y_test_pred[i])/y_test[i]\n",
    "  sum = sum + np.abs(diff)   \n",
    "Test_MAPE = round(sum/n*100,2)\n",
    "print(\"Mean Absolute Percentage Error (MAPE) :\",Test_MAPE) "
   ]
